Lorraine Valentine suffers from the rare disease erythropoietic protoporphyria (EPP) which causes her skin to burn and become itchy when exposed to sunlight or UV light . 
  A holiday abroad left the 42-year-old in hospital for six days as the heat caused her entire body to swell . 
  Her sun allergy means she has to keep herself completely covered as even a small dose of sun on her skin leaves her in pain . 
  The condition is caused by a build-up of a chemical in the blood . 
 